news.title: Indiabulls Housing gets committee nod to raise up to Rs 50,000 crore via bonds
news.para: ​As per the existing shareholders' enabling authorisation, valid up to July 28, 2022, the company can raise funds up to Rs 50,000 crore through issuance of secured or unsecured non-convertible debentures (NCDs or bonds) in one or more tranches on a private placement basis.

news.title: Mumbai: Panel for buildings with part or no OC within a month
news.para: Shinde, in a written reply to Prabhu’s query, said there are 728 buildings across Mumbai that have been granted part OC and owe the BMC approximately Rs 1,018 crore in form of various taxes.

news.title: Income tax department searches premises of Hiranandani Group
news.para: ​​On Tuesday, the directorate of I-T investigation, Mumbai, formed teams that arrived at the premises in the morning for the search; it will continue for a few days, it is learnt.

news.title: CREDAI-NCR members plan to stop construction works due to hike in raw material price
news.para: In a statement, CREDAI-NCR said the cost of raw materials has gone up by a weighted average of about 30 to 40 per cent recently while the cost of few items has increased by more than 100 per cent in the last 2 years.

news.title: China Evergrande to resolve $511 million trust loan with state help: Sources
news.para: Under the loan resolution, CITIC will return the land used as collateral to Evergrande, the world's most indebted property developer, who will then pass it on to the Guangzhou city government to put up for sale, the sources said.

news.title: Japan's land prices rebound in 2021 as economy recovers from COVID hit
news.para: Overall, average land prices gained 0.6% in 2021, data from Japan's land ministry showed on Tuesday, following a 0.5% drop in 2020, which marked the first decline in six years.

news.title: I-T department detects Rs 3,000-crore worth cash transactions after raids on Omaxe group
news.para: "The search action covered more than 45 premises in Delhi and NCR, Chandigarh, Ludhiana, Lucknow and Indore," the statement issued by the policy-making body for the tax department said.

news.title: China Evergrande says lenders lay claim over $2.1 billion
news.para: It announced Tuesday that one of its key units Evergrande Property Services Group had about $2.1 billion in cash that banks have laid claim to as security guarantees via a third party, a discovery made when the company was doing its annual report.

news.title: Frame rules to allot TNHB houses for young lawyers: Madras HC
news.para: The court passed the order on a plea moved by advocate P Subburaj for a direction to the Tamil Nadu Housing Board to allot a house under the public quota for rent at Tower Block, Taylors Road, Kilpauk, Chennai.

news.title: Kolkata Metro green light for New Barrackpore link
news.para: Once the entire Yellow Line is operational, the southern point of Metro — New Garia or Kavi Subhas — will get connected to the northern end, Barasat. For now, it will go up to New Barrackpore.

news.title: Indore: Court directs police to register fraud case against builder
news.para: The court of judicial magistrate first class Firoz Akhtar directed police to register a case of forgery against builder Dwarikadheesh Agarwal, his wife and two employees Anand Vyas and Nilesh Jaiswal.

news.title: Jaipur metro begins move to revise phase-II plan
news.para: A JMRC official said, “The Jaipur Metro phase II on Tonk road is conflicting with JDA’s signal-free project. As some modifications are required, the DPR will be revised again after the survey.”

news.title: DevX sets up 90,000-sq-ft coworking center in Vadodara
news.para: According to Umesh Uttamchandani, Co-Founder – DevX, the size of the new center is an indication of the company’s optimism on the next wave of growth from tier II cities of Gujarat and India.

news.title: Haryana CM recommends CBI probe into Chintels Paradiso incident
news.para: Two women were killed after the dining room floor of a sixth-floor apartment at Chintels Paradiso in Sector 109 came down on February 10, triggering the collapse of roofs and floors directly under it, till the first floor.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body seals 210 units over property tax dues
news.para: So far, the tax department has sealed 1,291 properties in the East Zone under its ongoing drive. The department has also issued notices to 11,658 property owners.
